            <title>[LU-3176] linux md raid-6 read-error correction in degraded state</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3176</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;md raid6 is not doing correct read-error when single disk failed and going to be degraded mode for one more drive. I think original code only considered raid5, but did&apos;t work for raid6.&lt;br/&gt;
This is fixed in mainstream linux kernel.&lt;br/&gt;
